<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Skyfeeds.org</title>
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0-alpha1/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.6;
      margin: 20px;
      background-color: #d3d3d3; /* Light gray background */
      background-size: 100px; /* Smaller moon */
      background-repeat: no-repeat;
      background-position: top right; /* Top right position */
      background-attachment: fixed;
      color: #333;
    }

    h1, h2, h3 {
      color: #333;
    }

    .btn-ical {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 5px;
      background-color: #007BFF;
      color: white;
      border: none;
      padding: 10px 15px;
      border-radius: 5px;
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    .btn-ical:hover {
      background-color: #0056b3;
      color: white;
    }

    .btn-ical i {
      font-size: 1.2em;
    }

    .eclipse-section {
      margin-top: 30px;
      padding: 20px;
      background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
      border-radius: 8px;
    }

    .eclipse-nav {
      margin-top: 20px;
    }

    table {
      width: 100%;
      margin-top: 15px;
      border-collapse: collapse;
    }

    th, td {
      padding: 8px 12px;
      text-align: left;
      border: 1px solid #ddd;
    }

    th {
      background-color: #f2f2f2;
    }

    tr:nth-child(even) {
      background-color: #f9f9f9;
    }

    .type-title {
      text-transform: capitalize;
    }

    @media (max-width: 767px) {
      .btn-label-full { display: none; }
    }

    @media (min-width: 768px) {
      .btn-label-short { display: none; }
    }

    details.collapsible-panel {
      margin-top: 20px;
      background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 0;
    }

    details.collapsible-panel > summary {
      cursor: pointer;
      padding: 14px 20px;
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: #333;
      list-style: none;
      border-radius: 8px;
      user-select: none;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 12px;
    }

    details.collapsible-panel > summary .summary-title {
      flex: 1;
    }

    details.collapsible-panel > summary .summary-actions {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 6px;
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      font-weight: normal;
    }

    details.collapsible-panel > summary::-webkit-details-marker {
      display: none;
    }

    details.collapsible-panel > summary::after {
      content: " ▼";
      font-size: 0.8em;
      color: #666;
    }

    details.collapsible-panel[open] > summary::after {
      content: " ▲";
    }

    details.collapsible-panel > .collapsible-body {
      padding: 0 20px 20px;
    }

    /* On desktop the "how to use" guidance is always visible — no toggle needed */
    @media (min-width: 768px) {
      details#how-to-use > summary {
        display: none;
      }

      details#how-to-use > .collapsible-body {
        display: block;
        padding: 0;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="container">
  <h1>Skyfeeds</h1>

  <p>
    Welcome to <strong>Skyfeeds.org</strong>, your source for upcoming solar and lunar eclipses in
    iCal format.
  </p>

  <details id="how-to-use" class="collapsible-panel" style="margin-bottom: 24px;">
    <summary>How to use this page</summary>
    <div class="collapsible-body">
      <p>
        This page provides a comprehensive list of upcoming solar and lunar eclipses, including their
        dates, peak times, types, and visibility across different continents and countries.
        The solar eclipses are categorized by continent and country, allowing you to find specific
        events relevant to your location. Lunar eclipses are considered global and are listed with
        their types.
      </p>
      <p>
        Also given are links for "All celestial events" for countries/continents. It is an iCal that
        has all total solar eclipses for that country/continent and all lunar eclipses.
        If you are unsure what you want, you should probably go for the global "All Solar and Lunar
        Eclipses"
        link. They are not that common, so it won't swamp your calendar (maybe one or two events a
        year).
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>What are iCal files?</strong><br>
        iCal files (<code>.ics</code>) are a standard format for sharing calendar events. You can
        subscribe to or import
        these files into your favorite calendar app (such as Google Calendar, Apple Calendar, or
        Outlook)
        to keep track of upcoming solar and lunar eclipses. To add an iCal file to your calendar,
        right click
        on the link and copy the URL, then import it into your calendar app.
      </p>

      <p>
        Here is how it looks when doing it with Google:<br><br>
        <img src="google_calendar_import.png" alt="Google Calendar Import" style="width: 500px">
      </p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <% continents = solar_eclipses.flat_map(&:continents).uniq.sort %>
  <% countries = solar_eclipses.flat_map(&:countries).uniq.sort %>
  <%
    calendar_icon = <<~HTML
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" fill="currentColor" class="bi bi-rss" viewBox="0 0 16 16">
        <path d="M14 1a1 1 0 0 1 1 1v12a1 1 0 0 1-1 1H2a1 1 0 0 1-1-1V2a1 1 0 0 1 1-1zM2 0a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v12a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V2a2 2 0 0 0-2-2z"/>
        <path d="M5.5 12a1.5 1.5 0 1 1-3 0 1.5 1.5 0 0 1 3 0m-3-8.5a1 1 0 0 1 1-1c5.523 0 10 4.477 10 10a1 1 0 1 1-2 0 8 8 0 0 0-8-8 1 1 0 0 1-1-1m0 4a1 1 0 0 1 1-1 6 6 0 0 1 6 6 1 1 0 1 1-2 0 4 4 0 0 0-4-4 1 1 0 0 1-1-1"/>
      </svg>
    HTML
  %>

  <!-- Global Feeds Section -->
  <div class="download-section eclipse-section">
    <h2>Global Eclipse Feeds</h2>

    <p>
      These feeds cover <strong>all eclipses worldwide</strong>, with no location filtering.
      If you're not sure where to start, subscribe to <strong>All Solar and Lunar Eclipses</strong>
      — eclipses aren't that common (maybe one or two a year) so it won't fill up your calendar.
    </p>
    <div class="mb-3">
      <a href="all/all_all.ics" class="btn-ical" target="_blank">
        <%= calendar_icon %>
        <span class="btn-label-full">All Solar and Lunar Eclipses</span>
        <span class="btn-label-short">All Solar+Lunar</span>
      </a>
      <a href="all/all_solar_all.ics" class="btn-ical" target="_blank">
        <%= calendar_icon %>
        <span class="btn-label-full">All Solar Eclipses</span>
        <span class="btn-label-short">All Solar</span>
      </a>
      <a href="all/all_lunar_all.ics" class="btn-ical" target="_blank">
        <%= calendar_icon %>
        <span class="btn-label-full">All Lunar Eclipses</span>
        <span class="btn-label-short">All Lunar</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Page Structure Section -->
  <div class="eclipse-section">
    <h2>Browse by Type and Region</h2>
    <p>
      The rest of this page breaks eclipses down in two ways. First by <strong>type</strong>
      — lunar eclipses are visible from anywhere on the night side of Earth, so they get their
      own global feed. Solar eclipses are only visible from a narrow path, so they are further
      broken down by <strong>region</strong>: you can browse by continent or drill down to
      a specific country to find the events and feeds most relevant to you.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Lunar Eclipses Section -->
  <details id="lunar-eclipses" class="collapsible-panel">
    <summary>
      <span class="summary-title">Lunar Eclipses</span>
      <span class="summary-actions" onclick="event.stopPropagation()">
        <a href="all/all_lunar_all.ics" class="btn-ical" target="_blank">
            <%= calendar_icon %>
            <span class="btn-label-full">All Lunar Eclipses</span>
            <span class="btn-label-short">All</span>
          </a>
      </span>
    </summary>
    <div class="collapsible-body">
      <table class="table table-striped">
        <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Date</th>
          <th class="type-title">Type</th>
          <th>Link</th>
        </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
        <% lunar_eclipses.each do |eclipse| %>
          <tr>
            <td><%= eclipse.date %></td>
            <td class="type-title"><%= eclipse.type %></td>
            <td><a href="<%= eclipse.url %>" target="_blank">Details</a></td>
          </tr>
        <% end %>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </details>

  <!-- Solar Eclipses Section -->
  <div id="solar-eclipses" class="eclipse-section">
    <h2>Solar Eclipses</h2>

    <p>
      Here are the upcoming solar eclipses categorized by continent and country.
    </p>

    <h3>By continent</h3>
    <% continents.each do |continent| %>
      <details class="collapsible-panel">
        <summary id="<%= continent.downcase %>">
          <span class="summary-title"><%= continent %></span>
          <span class="summary-actions" onclick="event.stopPropagation()">
            <a href="<%= continent.downcase.tr(' ', '_') %>/<%= continent.downcase.tr(' ', '_') %>_all.ics" class="btn-ical" target="_blank">
              <%= calendar_icon %>
              <span class="btn-label-full">All Celestial Events</span>
              <span class="btn-label-short">All</span>
            </a>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="collapsible-body">
          <table class="table table-striped mt-3">
            <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Date</th>
              <th>Peak Time</th>
              <th class="type-title">Type</th>
              <th>Countries with visibility</th>
              <th>Link</th>
            </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            <% continent_eclipses = solar_eclipses.select { |e| e.continents.include?(continent) } %>
            <% continent_eclipses.each do |eclipse| %>
              <tr>
                <td><%= eclipse.date %></td>
                <td><%= eclipse.time.strftime('%H:%M:%S') %> (UTC)</td>
                <td class="type-title"><%= eclipse.type %></td>
                <td>
                  <% eclipse.countries.each do |country| %>
                    <a href="#<%= country.downcase.tr(' ', '_') %>"><%= country %></a>
                    <% if country != eclipse.countries.last %>,
                    <% end %>
                  <% end %>
                </td>
                <td><a href="<%= eclipse.url %>" target="_blank">Details</a></td>
              </tr>
            <% end %>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </details>
    <% end %>
    <h3 class="mt-5">Solar Eclipses by Country</h3>
    <% countries.each do |country| %>
      <details class="collapsible-panel">
        <summary id="<%= country.downcase.tr(' ', '_') %>">
          <span class="summary-title"><%= country %></span>
          <span class="summary-actions" onclick="event.stopPropagation()">
            <a href="<%= country.downcase.tr(' ', '_') %>/<%= country.downcase.tr(' ', '_') %>_all.ics" class="btn-ical" target="_blank">
              <%= calendar_icon %>
              <span class="btn-label-full">All Celestial Events</span>
              <span class="btn-label-short">All</span>
            </a>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="collapsible-body">
          <table class="table table-striped mt-3">
            <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Date</th>
              <th>Peak Time</th>
              <th class="type-title">Type</th>
              <th>Continents</th>
              <th>Link</th>
            </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            <% country_eclipses = solar_eclipses.select { |e| e.countries.include?(country) } %>
            <% country_eclipses.each do |eclipse| %>
              <tr>
                <td><%= eclipse.date %></td>
                <td>
                  <% local_time = local_time_for_country.call(eclipse, country) %>
                  <%= local_time.strftime('%H:%M:%S') %> (<%= country_timezone.call(country) %>)
                </td>
                <td class="type-title"><%= eclipse.type %></td>
                <td>
                  <% eclipse.continents.each do |c| %>
                    <a href="#<%= c.downcase %>"><%= c %></a>
                    <% if c != eclipse.continents.last %>,
                    <% end %>
                  <% end %>
                </td>
                <td><a href="<%= eclipse.url %>" target="_blank">Details</a></td>
              </tr>
            <% end %>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </details>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>
<br>
<br>
<center>
  <h4>Data used with thanks from
    <a href="https://eclipse.gsfc.nasa.gov/SKYCAL/SKYCAL.html">Sky Events Calendar by Fred Espenak
      and Sumit Dutta (NASA's GSFC)</a></h4>
  <p>
    This is an open-source project hosted on GitHub.
    Visit the repository at <a href="https://github.com/hlascelles/skyfeeds.org">https://github.com/hlascelles/skyfeeds.org</a>
  </p>
</center>
</body>
</html>
